This article is about an executive order issued by President Joseph R. Biden Jr. The order emphasizes the importance of domestic manufacturing and the commercialization of federally funded inventions in the United States. It states that new technologies and products developed with support from the U.S. government should be manufactured in the U.S. whenever feasible and consistent with applicable law. The order also calls for coordination and consultation among different government agencies and stakeholders to implement this policy. It encourages agencies to consider domestic manufacturing in their research and development funding agreements and to support small businesses in transitioning technologies to commercial markets. The order also includes provisions for modernizing the reporting of invention utilization and securing critical and emerging technologies through domestic manufacturing. It calls for agencies to develop a waiver process for the domestic manufacturing requirements and to establish guidelines for negotiating with waiver applicants. The order also requires agencies to submit reports on their implementation of the order and its effectiveness.